Karl,

I'm just as confused as you, however think that your conclusion is
correct.  That is, the fidonet.org people should better support their
domain in the MX records.  

It may not be possible for them to do that ... unfortunately.  I don't
know how their stuff is implemented at ucar, but they might not have
enough "talent" to manage lots of gateways all over the country.

And I was thinking of adding path shortcutting to MMDF's uucp channel
along the lines you described ... oh well.


